    • interpretAction

      public void interpretAction(Action playerChosenAction, GameInfo currentGameState, PlayerInGame playerState)
      This method will get called if POST on games/{gameId}/players/{playerName}/actions/{actionId}. SplendorActionListGenerator (lookUpActions) -> Map from hashed string to action - {actionId} -> Action playerChosenAction, so we can know prior to this method called, we can find the Action the player wants to execute TODO: Note: we only provide ValidActions to players, so execution can never failed
      Parameters:
      playerChosenAction - generated from
      currentGameState - current game state that might be changed from this action execution
      playerState - the player specific game state that might be changed from this action execution
